userPromptTemplate:
Generate a 'Read in Daily Life' module for TOEFL Reading (2026 new format).

Module: {{module}}
Text types to use: {{textTypes}}
CEFR level: {{cefrLevel}}
Target word count per text: {{wordCount}}
Distractor difficulty: {{distractorDifficulty}}

Module guidelines:
- module1: 2 texts × 2-3 questions each (factual + inference). CEFR B1-B2. Medium distractors.
- module2Hard: 2 texts × 2-3 questions each (inference-heavy, attitude/intent). CEFR B2-C1. High distractors (2 options very close in meaning).
- module2Easy: 2 texts × 2-3 questions each (mostly factual, simple inference). CEFR A2-B1. Low distractors (clear wrong answers).

Include at least 1 inference question per module (implied meaning, not directly stated).

Respond with this exact JSON structure:
{
  "texts": [
    {
      "id": "t1",
      "textType": "email",
      "content": "string — the full text",
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "q1",
          "stem": "string — the question",
          "options": ["A. ...", "B. ...", "C. ...", "D. ..."],
          "correctIndex": 0,
          "type": "factual|inference|purpose",
          "explanation": "string — why the correct answer is right"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
